    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uninitialized buffer access in NGAP transport layer address conversion\n\n### Summary\nThe NGAP gNB procedures contained a potential segmentation fault when handling PDU session setup responses with zero-length transport layer addresses. The issue occurred in the `allocAddrCopy` function which failed to properly initialize the output `BIT_STRING_t` structure when the input transport layer address had zero length.\n\nThis led to downstream code accessing uninitialized buffer pointers and size fields, causing undefined behavior and potential crashes during PDU session establishment procedures.\n\nThe bug was particularly evident when handling PDU sessions with dynamically assigned transport addresses that hadn't been resolved yet.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_nas_procedures.c`: Enhanced `allocAddrCopy` function to always initialize output structure fields\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_nas_procedures.c`: Added validation checks before accessing transport layer address buffers in debug logging\n\n"
}